You're off to a very good start. One request that's pretty standard here is that you make a .love file and upload it with your post, so the time investment of people downloading and trying out your code is so low that everyone will do it. Also, enjoy working with Love and Lua, learn as much as you can, read everything you can get your hands on, search the forum because a lot of things have been talked about and a lot of questions have been answered, ask lots of your own questions. Welcome to the community!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=319">Inny</a> — Thu Dec 20, 2012 5:09 am</p><hr />
